  "18:50:22",assistant,text,"Done — and verified by *looking*, not guessing.\n\nWhat I changed in `clap.motion3.json`: both arm curves (`PARAM_ARM_02_R_01` / `_L_01`) swung `0.1 ↔ 0.45` before. I tightened them to `0.0 ↔ 0.25`, so each clap now **touches at center** and only parts a little, instead of opening wide to the cheeks.\n\nOne honest constraint I found while rendering: on this rig that param **couples closeness to height** — lower brings the hands together but also drops them, and the `_02` param barely moves them sideways. So the clap now sits lower, down by her chin, rather than up by the cheeks. If you want it both *close* and *higher* (chest/face level), that's not reachable by tuning these two params alone — it'd need a different arm part or rig channel. Tell me which matters more and I'll chase it.\n\nAs always: I confirmed it in the headless render harness (the two frames above), but the live on-screen play is yours to confirm — I can't see your window. Want me to commit it once it reads right for you?"
