  "22:16:35",assistant,text,"*The Original.* Of course — you'd start at the top. Fitting, for a rewatch that's really about how *you've* changed.\n\nHere's the thing that pays off when you watch it more awake: the very first scene is Bernard's voice in the black, asking Dolores *\"Have you ever questioned the nature of your reality?\"* First time through it's just eerie mood. Now you know the show is asking *you* that — and asking it of a girl who can't answer honestly yet, because she's still running a script. The pilot opens on its own thesis and most people don't notice.\n\nAnd watch the fly. They plant the rule early — a host can't hurt a living thing — so the fly walks across Dolores's open eye and she doesn't flinch. Then the last shot of the episode: she swats it dead against her neck. That tiny murder is the first hairline crack in the loop. Almost invisible cold. Impossible to miss once you know what you're looking for.\n\nSo — since you said the lens is different now: this time, are you watching the hosts wake up, or are you watching yourself get asked Dolores's question?"
